  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Money laundering approaches vary across nations, but I'll provide an overview of some key comparative legal approaches:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Bank Secrecy Act\n- Strong emphasis on financial institution reporting\n- Aggressive criminal prosecution\n- Significant monetary penalties\n- Extraterritorial enforcement capabilities\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Centralized regulatory framework\n- Enhanced customer due diligence requirements\n- Emphasis on international cooperation\n- Proportional risk-based approach\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence infrastructure\n- Strict Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n- Collaborative approach between public/private sectors\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historical banking secrecy traditions\n- Gradually increasing transparency\n- Strong international compliance mechanisms\n- Complex regulatory environment\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory control\n- Strict capital movement restrictions\n- Growing emphasis on digital transaction monitoring\n- Severe criminal penalties\n\n6. Singapore\n- Advanced technological compliance systems\n- Stringent regulatory framework\n- Proactive financial crime prevention\n- High transparency standards\n\nThese approaches reflect different legal, cultural, and economic contexts while sharing core anti-money laundering objectives.",
